The paper deals with user authentication on smartphones, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach uses a deep learning architecture (Siamese Long Short-Term Memory network), which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the usability and privacy concerns of traditional authentication mechanisms, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper uses sensor data from smartphones, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
